The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, April 19, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, April 19, 2004				 																																	Road to avoid				 																																	Prince Anwar Shah Road. One flank off Tollygunge Phari closed for laying pipes.				 																On stage				 																																	A pantomime show by Mouna Mukhar, directed by Santimoy Ray, and Pakhi, a play based on a Manoj Mitra work, staged by Youth Guild for Friendship, will be presented at Gorky Sadan, 6 pm onwards.				 																Bard talk 				 																																	Tagore scholar Basanti Mukhopadhyay will speak on Rabindranath O Paribesh Bhabana at Asiatic Society, at 4 pm.				 																Screenings				 																																	Some Secrets, Bellissima and Pleasant Days will be screened as part of the European Union Film Festival 2004, at Nandan, at 2.30 pm, 4.30 pm and 6.30 pm, respectively.
